text:
Wanted to have my dinner at the zi char stall. Ordered the bee hoon and the staff asked if want to add an egg and I told her okay.

The noodles was served cold and hard and felt like eating rubber bands. The only thing that's hot was the sunny side up. Highly likely the bee hoon was a canceled order and they served to me instead. Ate 2 mouths and that's it!

If any of you patronize this zi char stall, make sure they serve food hot.

I had my breakfast here on the 3rd day of Chinese New Year. I had to tell the lady at the counter 2 times what drinks I want and still she stares at me and I have to asked her again what as she doesn't tell me why she is not taking my order! Then she ask what drinkor what you want. Then I told her loudly what I want as twice she didn't hear me. Angry she bang all my drinks and all my drinks taste like water! Not happy to work during your Chinese new year period, don't work!
The Malay stall food is very nice. Try the lontong and nasi lemak!
